# Copy to `.env.development` or `.env.production` (or `.env.local` — gitignored).
#
# Game app origin (not the marketing landing URL) — no trailing slash. Used for social meta tags
# and (in production builds) absolute manifest start_url / scope for the PWA.
#   VITE_SITE_ORIGIN=https://draught-game.netlify.app/
#
# Same contract as draught-fe: API base includes `/api` if your backend serves at /api/.
#
# Development (with Vite proxy in vite.config.ts — requires Django on localhost:8000):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
#
# Development (Vite only, calling hosted API — avoids proxy / ECONNREFUSED if Django is off):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com/api
#
# Production (hosted backend):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api
#
# Optional — Google Form (or any URL) for bug reports / feedback (shows in nav when set):
#   VITE_FEEDBACK_FORM_URL=https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/.../viewform
